I disagree with the statement that "Huxley Steel producing 100 gallons of sewage caused the river to get polluted today." The pollution of the river was caused by the combined sewage output of both Huxley Steel and Huxley Lumber, which totaled 200 gallons. Each plant individually producing 100 gallons contributed equally to the pollution, so both are equally responsible. Therefore, attributing the pollution solely to Huxley Steel's production overlooks the fact that Huxley Lumber also contributed an equal amount to the sewage that exceeded the treatment capacity.
They are both equally responsible in this case, it isn't fair to say either one "caused" it.
